A rogue can slaughter a druid if he's twinked/simply well equipped high level, but the druid has to assume the position for that close-range fight to ever take place. <br>
<br>
Refusing to engage someone who you cannot cast on isn't being a pansy.  It's &quot;not commiting suicide.&quot;  If the Druid/caster is the one who instigated the fight, you can mock him for running if you want.  If a druid doesn't want to fight your 120s resist monster with 10 pillage wands, he won't.  If you try to annoy him about it, he can ignore you, or at worst say to hell with it and go port to the other side of the world.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upoisindaggerfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PoisinDaggerfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/23/01 11:54:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arenas</span><hr size=1> Golem wands are easy to get and are instant cast at the same range as any caster spell.  Unload one or 2 of them and you strip off a druids DS and sow... hence, he will never outrun you if he tries to recast sow, or land a dot/nuke cast, and by that time you can stick him with a root poison/blind poison.  Fight over in 30 secs or less.<br>
<br>
And if you are fighting a druid/caster, I drop all AC gear for dragon gear (MR/CR/FR/HP), so even if they get an offensive cast off, it gets resisted.  Untwinked, you can get resists up to 100-150 and add 200-400 hps.<br>
<br>
If you are thinking in straight melee over caster, the key factor why rogues excell above all others in a prepared PvP setting is the poisons that can be applied.<br>
<br>
Golem wands+jboots=caster beatdown<br>
<br>
Note: Mages are a pain, but I found the best way is to target the mage while having applied a root poison and golem wand off his DS and sow.  His pet will attack you and when you ripost the pet, it will get the root poison.  Then start picking away at him with arrows or your dagger of choice... SBD comes in real handy here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p>
Poisin Daggerfist,
60th Assassin- Retired</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiamwotan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>I am Wotan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Wotan_Rogue/yinyang.gif border=0 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/01 6:34:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Wotan_Rogue/mask2a.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arenas</span><hr size=1> What sterk, ceescrit, and wiggo said.<br>
<br>
If you really want to go all out, get some potions: haste, sow, resist, and regen.  Definitely pumice his buffs and use a bow vs. Damage shield.<br>
<br>
If your MR is <100 odds are he'll land a snare if he can chain cast it.<br>
<br>
If you can choose the venue, pick someplace enclosed without room to maneuver. <br>
<br>
